      "content": "It's not that melatonin and zolpidem won't work together; it's just that taking them together can lead to increased drowsiness and potentially dangerous side effects. Melatonin is naturally occurring and works by regulating your sleep-wake cycle, while zolpidem is a prescription medication that enhances GABA activity to promote sleep. When combined, they may result in excessive sedation or even respiratory depression. To improve your sleep, it's best to stick with one strategy that suits you best. If you're struggling with insomnia, consider trying a sleep routine, relaxation techniques, or consulting your doctor for alternative solutions.",
      "source": "target",
